<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100351941123655></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100351941123655><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=12&mid=100351941123655>RE: fear</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=12&mid=100351941123655#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=887><span id=Sage>Zuranthium</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>385 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Oct 19th 3:23 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.73]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Wha, wha, wha. I can't do something that another class can do. You want something that someone else has and you don't.<br><br>Even if they gave mages fear vs. summoned things, it wouldn't be of much use. Almost all summoned things are outdoors in crowded areas, or in dungeons. Fear is not a good thing in crowded places when you don't have snare. And even if you DO have snare, it is not a good idea for when you are in a dungeon. Just stick to using your dismiss summoned line to do damage. Mages are supposed to dish out lots of damage, not make things run away.<br><br>Former EQ Addict.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
