	   <tr><td colspan=2>There are several posts talking about what race to choose.  Oone thing they all try and point out is that Erudites and Humans are inferior because they cant see in the dark.  Tis is an obsurd notioon considering at 16 you get Summon Heatstone, and it can be put in the ammo slot so if you have something better in the neck slot you can still use one.  <br><br>Now the Attributes.  Most casters will put 25 in to Int and 5 in to str.  As a mage I feel this is unnecessary, and the points could be better spent on Dex or Cha.  The reason being is that you should never have to worry about being encumbered due to Summoned Weight free bags.  These used to suck because they would disappear if you got booted, so it wasn't worth risking losing all you nicely aquired loot, but they fixed that so you have a half an hour after you log before everything disappears.  Just dont forget to sell... he he.(I've done that)  <br><br>So then the advantages of race now.  I'll start with my 2 favorite choices.  Most of this stuff you should already know and it's just rehashing but....<br><br>Erudites have the best starting Int, By a LONG shot, and Int is the name of the game for casters.  Plus Paineel, just a short hop from Erudin is a Fantastic newbie zone, especially for casters.  millions of non-agroing mobs, collect bat wings and bone chips up the wazoo in your first 4 levels and you can sell them to upwards of 5 plat a stack, enough to buy all your spells for the first few levels.<br><br>Gnomes even though it is stated they have the 3rd highest Int, they only trail the 2nd by 1.   1!!!!  not that big of a deal.  The 2 main advantages of gnomes are they are not KOS by eveil races, except Iksar.  I have wandered thru Neriak and Ogguk many a time without having to do anything to raise faction.  A very big advantage, especially if you want to do the Stein of Muggok Quest. And you get tinkering skill.  Which can be interesting.  Yes the newbie zone sucks but it is only a short run to Gfay.  Plus its nice having  a Library in your hometown so you have good faction when buying those expensive summoning spells.  <br><br>High Elf has the advantage of High Char to start off with.  if you get a crude stein and maybe one more Cha buffer you can end up getting the best prices for your Goods VERY easily, and it can make a   sizable difference.  42 with ally faction was offered 90 plat.  Same item by High elf with maxed out char and indiferent faction was offered 113 plat.  That is a full 20th level spell for one item.  Another advantage is a very high wisdom so you will succeed on your skills more, and since you have amazing high int at higher levels your skill will also raise quickly<br><br>Dark elf  too much of a pain in the @SS to play in my opinoin, KOS everywhere and a confusing home town for 1 extra point of Int?  mind you, if you like playing dark elves, more power to you, I jsut dont see any advantage to having one<br><br>Humans......suck..... there is way too much int to make up compared to the other races, and even though they have more rounded stats and  a higher str, like I pointed out earlier, the str is really inconsiquential, so that really doesnt contribute a whole lot.<br>And yes you can make up the Int loss in the long run, but that woulod take away from the Resist gear that you are going to NEED at higher levels.<br><br>In conclusion, even though some people have been trashing the mage class saying they are useless after whatever level....the mage class can be the most fun to play of all the calsses, because there is a lot of strategy, and if you have a good personality and get yourself known and make friends (aside from joining a guild) you should have NO problems getting in to a group.  And if you use the right resources (eqmagecompendium)  there is a ton of knowlege on how to solo succesfully if you cant find a group, instead of whining about how you can't find one.<br><br>Maybe some people with bad people and pet skills ruined it for the rest of us, but if you can show a group that you can coontrol your pet, and that you are a fun person to be with,, we can change the minds of some of the more closed minded people (who think that a group should consist of..... instead of he's a good player, lets get him!)<br><br>Inestyne<br>Mage Extrordinaire<br>Tarew Marr<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
