	   <tr><td colspan=2>It doesn't really matter what race you choose too much.  Just choose the race you like the best. Don't pick a race just because they have the 'best' stats. However, if you are a newbie I DO recommend that you start as a High Elf or Gnome, simply becuase it is easier to learn the game as those races (infravision and you start out in Feydwer).<br><br>I agree with you that some stupid people sometimes ruin the name of the magician. They say that pets are totally useless at high levels becuase you are always in dungeons and pets always screw up in dungeon. Well, this is true to some extent. HOWEVER, you can still use your pets just fine in many dungeons. It is just a few dungeons where there is bad pathing for pets, and stupid people make it sound like pets are worthless everywhere.<br><br>If you know how to control your pet, and if you are in a guild then you won't have many problems grouping. Now, it IS true that mages aren't at the first pick for higher level groups, but they are still just fine, and people that complain about never being able to get a group either - A. had one or two bad experiences with not being able to get a group, so they made it sound like it was that bad ALL the time; or - B. they are jackasses so nobody WANTS to group with them; or - C. They spent so much time soloing that they don't know many people and they don't know how to work well in groups, so people won't take them into their groups.<br><br>Just have fun playing, and don't try to just keep leveling and leveling, you won't have nearly as much fun with the game if you do that. <br><br>Former EQ Addict.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
