	   <tr><td colspan=2>While looking here I see a trend of posts that involve "Mages = useless", and so forth.  I didn&#8217;t see any from about a year or so ago, but here lately I have seen a lot of people that are feeling this way, myself included.  I also have to agree that the mage class is useless post 50 and will explain in this post.<br><br>The reason for looking here is for that one spot that is easy and fast because my downtime is what kills me from the idea of soloing. At 53 its not easy to do. I want something that I can kill fast with little mana.  The best thing I have found is Cendryela (sp) in the ferrott at the PoF portal.  She will die quick and easy, and you only use 1 bub of mana doing it.  Also, by the time she repops your FM again.<br><br>Here is the sad thing...I cant get to her unless there is a PoF raid on and all the specks are clear from the maze to the portal or I will die.  I have tried to get back there to her with my pet but when I attack the one down the tunnel I get 4 more agro on me.<br><br>So, now I have a "ok" solo spot that I cant get to.  What now?  Go LFG? NOT!<br><br>I have been playing my mage for 40 days Game time, and have been playing for over 2 years RL.  I have found that after all this time, It was a waste of time.<br><br>From lvl 1 to 45 was great.  After that it was crap.  I stopped soloing around 30 because it just wasn&#8217;t possible. Downtime was horrible, and the mobs were just too hard to kill.  My pet cant tank and taunt good, nukes get too much agro....so I started looking for groups.  I did ok till I hit 45.  Even 45 wasn&#8217;t so bad compared to 50+.  When I hit 50, it was all over.  I tried to solo (ferrott) that didn&#8217;t happen, I tried LFG- FYI - MAGES ARE NOT WANTED/NEEDED AT ALL POST 50.  Let me tell you now...you will spend hours and hours looking for groups with a 50-54 mage.<br><br>Sometimes I get on and pay for ports to 4 or 5 zones with LFG on and shouts to the zone "Lvl 53 Mage LFG" for hours and never get a answer/tell one that they can use me.  Put yourself on list all you want...you&#8217;ll never hear from that person again.<br><br>You think being in a guild will help? LOL!  Only your closest RL (real life) friends will help you with lvling.  Even your guild don&#8217;t need you, and if they do its for Molt rods only.<br><br>You are not needed in a group.  You will not be needed in a group until you hit 55+ when you get CoH (call of the hero).  So from 45 to 55 your in the worst HELL you will ever know.  No one wants you, your not needed, your pet isn&#8217;t needed, your not needed on raids...etc. You get the point.  Its sad, really sad that you have wasted all that time leveling your mage to get thrown to the curb.<br><br>So if you think its fun to solo/grp to 50 then go ahead.  You will find it HARD to get to 60 with a mage and most likely get it alone if you do.<br><br>Your options--<br>1. Get a group of friends to group with every day you can.<br><br>2. Solo Solo Solo<br><br>3. Play for the rest of your life solo/grouping for that pixel of exp a day.<br><br>Let me also tell you...at lvl 51+, its hell all the way to the top.  Sometimes when you get really really really lucky and get in a group, you don&#8217;t even see that exp bar go up at all!!<br><br>If you are thinking about creating a mage, do it because its fun up to 45.  After that you will not be needed and you will find yourself starting a new char.  It that doesn&#8217;t sound fun to you, then don&#8217;t create a mage...they suck after 45/50.<br><br>If I had to do it all again...I would have created a 1. enchanter 2.cleric 3.war.<br><br>To all those (too late now) mages out there, Stick it out to 55 for your guild.  Even if they wont help you.  You will be needed for CoH and molt rods.  Then you can create another char and level it up and have fun to 60 with it.  I created a war a long time ago and I chose to level it up because my guild needed more of them.<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
