<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100251686594788></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100251686594788><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=12&mid=100251686594788>RE: Unloved Mages?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=12&mid=100251686594788#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Oct 8th 12:54 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>In my opinion, the Erudite makes a more suitable Magician. The Erudins Base Stats for Intelligence is the highest availabe, and since Magicians are INT based casters then you made a great choice.<br>The more INT you have, the more Mana pool you have and all casters know, more mana = More power.<br><br>A Magician can solo very well. The Elemental pet being it's "Tank" to taunt while the Mage Nukes the dog snot out of the Mob. If done properly the Mage will die very few times, or atleast less then a class without a Pet for Taunting.<br><br>The way i have played my Mage is this:<br>Buff Self<br>Buff Pet<br>Summon Weapon and give it to the Pet, Give it 2 weapons at lvl 24. They duel weild 5 levels sooner then any other Pet class.<br>Sit and read your spell book to get Full Mana.<br><br>Now i am ready to seek out a Blue /con mob that is not a Roamer, more like the type that spawn at little huts, they are stationary.<br>If the spawn site has 2 or more Mobs, i can all of them, i pick the highest blue /con of the site.<br>Hot key /pet attack and use it.<br>When the Pet says "Taunting attacker Master" then Blast the current Mob. Use 2 types of DD spells too, so If one spell is recycling, cast the second one.<br>Now Important trick here.<br>DON'T RUN AWAY if you have out damaged the pet, then the Mob will turn to attack you, and you will most likely outrun your pet that cannot keep up with the mob at your back.<br>Instead, you want to press attack key and run "through" the mob, turn around and see the Pet is back in control and the Mob is either dead or your pet is nearly dead, but there you stand watching and not getting beat on.<br>Now by this time your either going to heal your pet or let it die.<br><br>At higher levels it is important to know how to "Chain cast" pets, as thats the only way your going to survive those higher level UBER hitters.<br><br>At lower levels you either heal the pet, make a last ditch Nuke effort, or simply die.<br><br>To chain cast Pets:<br>1) Have lots of Malachite to spare.<br>2) Have enough Mana reserve for a Fizzle and Summoning the new Pet.<br>3) Stand close enough to your pet that it hears your commands.<br>4) Watch the pets health and know how long it will take to Fizzle + Recast a new pet, for me it is when the health bar is at the 4th letter of the pets name. For you are not me, so learn it.<br>5) Type out the command:  /pet get lost but don't hit enter yet, wait until you have used the most you can from the current pet, when you know the pet can only take say maybe another 8 attacks, and it has enough life to stay there long enough to Summon a new pet.<br>6) Start Summoning a new Pet, when step 5 is reached, and Just Before the casting time meter is about to give you that "You can only have one pet" message, HIT ENTER. =)<br>Your pet will suicide as you Command because it is either stupid, or very loyal.<br>and at that moment you have a Brand-spanky-new-full health-Meat Shield to command. =)<br><br>Best practice this 6 step method at an early level, cause you won't run fast, you won't tank that mob alone, and you surely won't be bound to that area cause you forgot to do it.<br><br>My Magician is now lvl 50. I have not played it to hear that Ding as fast as possible, i played it for the fun of the class, and i like how easy it is to collect Trade Skill items like HQ Bear skins, simply by telling the pet to attack, while i run to agro another mob.. Anyway. The Magician is also very group-able.<br>In a group you will do basically the same thing as the 6 steps above.. but you'll also be Damage Shielding 1 to 3 Tank types, Summoning Throwing Daggers, Summoning Arrows, Summoning Bandages, Summoning Food and Water, maybe a Heatstone, a Coldstone, or some other such thing, all while you have the comfort of knowing that your with 5 others to chat while your graciously sharing all that XP you could keep for yourself, doing it solo.<br><br>My magician can still count the number of times it was Grouped. It reached lvl 50 while killing Spiroc in Timorous Deep.<br><br>Magicians are a supply house for groups, or a very enjoyable Solo class, for when your Mad the Cleric was Playing "GEMS" and your screaming for a heal and they look up to see you do that Astral Projection trick, that out of body experience we all come to love.<br>Thats when i went total solo. That one Cleric, that one Very bad player of a Cleric,.. im still in therapy... i chat with my Pet now. =)<br><br>Have fun friend.. Being a Good Magician will prove ONE thing, when you "DING" you know you have done well and did not let yourself down. GRATS on that "DING" i heard all the way over on my server. =)<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
