	   <tr><td colspan=2>I'm sorry to say it but you will find grouping less and less post 50. At this stage of the game you can literally spend hours lfg and not get one. As of right now we are a non esential part of any group. Groups are constantly looking for a cleric, chanter, shaman, and 3 mele's. As for the summons we don't have any that are needed/wanted in the post 50 game. You can lvl to 60 grouping or solo but post 50 the exp solo isn't worth it. And the wait for a group drives most of us to another char. I currently have a 55th shaman that went from 1 to 51 in the amt of time it took my mage to go from 51 to 52.<br><br>As for raids we really arn't wanted due to the very little amt of dmg we do and bad pathing makes pets unwanted on most high lvl raids.<br><br>I have seen many raids where mage items rotted due to the raid saying no mages. Now if your lucky enough to manage a raid the main reason your there is to feed mod rods to the clerics/chanters (crack on a stick). And that is normally just when the cleric is having to res.<br><br>Don't get me wrong we can and are a very powerful class. And played right we can contribute to any group/raid. But getting past the pet pathing problem and bad mages letting the pets get away and pulling a train is very hard to do.<br><br>My biggest suggestion is to find a good guild early on learn to control the pet and group with guild and friends just as much as you possibly can. In many cases post 50 friends are what will get you a group.<br><br>Bedin Sowgood 55th Luminary (Povar)<br>Cilditin Barrteender 54th Elementalist (Povar)<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
