	   <tr><td colspan=2>Fellow mages of the art listen to my words of wisdom ( hehe always wanted to say that)<br>This guide is for all the little people who ask WHAT SHOULD I DO? well here it is.<br><br>Starting your character, first thing you have to do is choose a race, there are several options that<br>you can pick thru as a mage which are: Dark elf (evil kinda hard to play second best intelligence thoand starting town is very hard to get out of and get around in), Erudite(best intelligence rating but night blind (cant see a thing when its dark), High elf (forth best intelligence , infravision ( can see in dark ) and starting town is great for a newb), Gnome ( third best intelligence, infravision (cute too) :) Starting town is ok but not great ), Human ( in my opinion DO NOT BE A HUMAN IF YOUR GONNA BE A MAGE ( they are night blind, their stats are horrible, and they are ugly) Starting town is good though)...  <br><br>Ok now on to starting stats.... <br>Intelligence : The main skill of any caster ( SHD( not a caster but hey :p), MAG,ENC,NEC,WIZ), you learn all trade skills faster with higher int .,(at lvl 20 you get bonus exp according to your int rating ( I.E., 1 intelligence point gives you 10 mana))<br><br>Str: Determines how much you can carry ( pretty much useless to a caster),<br>Dont put anything into this stat for you will never need it that badly<br><br>Dex : Will help you with weapon procs ( but you dont really need that unless youve played EQ for a while and have items that actually proc)<br><br>Sta: Determines how long you can hold your breathe under water, and how many hps you have..( Do not put any points into this for it will not help you enuff to save your life).<br><br>Cha : determines ( for a mage) how much vendors sell you things for ( good but dont put anything into it)<br><br>Wis: Determines fizzles, and how much you fail at a skill ( if you want this is a good stat to put points into)<br><br>Agi: Determines extra AC and how fast you walk ( This is a great stat to put  points into)<br><br>Ok , now once you pick your stats race and of course class hit enter world ( for the newbs)...<br>once you have loaded up your new mage you have to go see your guild trainer ( right click one of the scrolls in your inventory) if you dont know the  way to your guild master type in """"/shout Can anyone help me to my guild master so i can train""""" and usually somone will help you out . ok once youve done that its time to pick a fight with something, since you have no money yet im not gonna tell you what to buy for your first level spells.<br><br>Once you find the zone out of your town ( if you cant type ""/shout Can somone help me out of this town please"", when you get out there will be gaurds by the end of the tunnel in which the town exits. Stay near these gaurds for they will save your life many times if you dont have good equipment. <br><br>OK, on to the newb fights........ When you are outside of your home town click on a roaming creature ( I.E. a decaying skelly, a Snake, a Rat etc..) and press the "c" button to consider them ( this means that it pretty much tells you if they will kill you if you fight them) DONT CLICK ON THE GUARDS!! hehe Well, if the creature cons black or white you can kill this at lvl 1 if it cons red or yellow it will eat you alive. do this till you get to lvl 4 and get some money, then its time to buy your spells,<br><br>Spells at lvl 1, Well i cant really advize you to buy any of the lvl one spells but it will help, My suggestion would be to go to www.castersrealm.com and look up Spell lists/ magician. <br><br> As a newbie magician you need to fight lvl 1-3 mobs to get to lvl 4. once you get to lvl 4, the fun starts, you get a pet at lvl 4 and if you have enough money buy all of them if not here is what you do: You buy the lvl 4 Water pet ( and your Direct damage spell ( ) Thats all you need till you get some money , and also when you get to lvl 4 train in meditate it is a must .<br><br>Ok well this is the best leveling guide youll ever read from 4 - 39 .. Well here it is......<br><br>LVL 4 : at lvl 4 you can go to the orc hill in Greater faydark ( awsome exp and kinda easy at your lvl) you can tag a orc that cons yellow and maybe if your lucky red. You bring it back to your spot that you set your pet down ( /pet guard here) and click your hot button ( /pet attack) which sends your pet in and you blast till its dead , if you get to many just run to the guards ( strifing and jumping ( CRTL + &lt; &gt; and space button). you can do this till lvl 8 and youll be fine and get lots of money :) ( If you havent figured out what spells to buy by now i cant help you because you dont deserve to play a mage. <br><br>LVL 8 Go into Crush bone kill Cents and pawns till 9 or 10 then get into a Wall group. You should be able to get to lvl 16 here but its not recommended because it gets REALLY boring after a while.<br><br>LVL 12 Go to oasis ( take the boat from Butcher block to Freeport ... Well look it up hehe ( WWW.Eqmaps.com)  ( Its self explanitory)). you can get into a Orc group at Orc highway ( watch out for sand giants) You can get to lvl 16 here.<br><br>LVL 16 Kick butt :) At lvl 16 you can go to LOIO ( lake of ill omen ) and fight sabertooth tigers ( con them first ) and you can take yellows which is awsome exp , and if you havent got much money the fangs they drop are worth 1-2pp each depending on  you CHA ( explained above) you can get to 21 here<br><br>LVL 21  Go to South Karana  and solo the hermit ( 3 minute spawn super easy with a pet and Awsome exp and loot) You can get to lvl 27 here.<br><br>LVL 27: go to Frontier mountains and fight mountain giants in a group you can get to lvl 30 here<br><br>LVL 30 - 39 Go to OT ( Over there) and get in a group i got out of lvl 30 ( hell LVL) in 5 hours ( awsome for a hell lvl) you can get to lvl 39 here after that im not sure :) <br><br>This guide is best as a good characters ( I.E. High elf, Gnome, erudite) ( Dark elfs can do this but its kinda hard) ( i dont include humans cause the only thing a human is good for is to be a death sheild for the good mages) &gt;:)<br><br><br>Akalnor Master of the elements<br>lvl 32 mage ( not for long ) <br>Terris Thule ( gimme a tell sometime) :)<br><br><br><br><br><br><br>&nbsp;<br>Akalnor Master of the elements<br>Terris Thule</td></tr>
