	   <tr><td colspan=2>This guy is Right about a few things, just wanted to expand.  I agree water is best for the reasons mentioned, (AC, Health, an so forth)   Some thing he forgot to mention though is the DD it casts.  The only other pet that has a DD is the Fire, and thats about useless at lower levels cause It dies almost immediately@! (snicker)  The DD, I have noticed, does make a sizable contribution to its damage output.  And as for the earth pet rooting?  A water pet can generally hold the MOB's agro even after a few well timed Nukes.  And if you do get agrod it will quickly regain Hate.  So take a few whacks and then back up, you're all set.  And it has much more HP to sustain a beating, unlike the fire.  Also the regen is very nice.  let an earth pet get beat down, and then compare its regen time to the water, you'll see what I mean.  My water pet almost never dies, only when I do something really stupid.  And that includes soloing low reds occasionally.<br><br>I hope this helps. <br><br>Inestyne<br>Mage extrordinaire<br>Tarew Marr<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
